A **block matrix** is partitioned into submatrices (blocks):
\[
A = \begin{pmatrix}
A_{11} & A_{12} & \cdots & A_{1m} \\
A_{21} & A_{22} & \cdots & A_{2m} \\
\vdots & \vdots & \ddots & \vdots \\
A_{m1} & A_{m2} & \cdots & A_{mm}
\end{pmatrix}
\]

If $A_{11}$ is nonsingular, block elimination gives:
\[
\begin{pmatrix} A_{11} & A_{12} \\ A_{21} & A_{22} \end{pmatrix}
= \begin{pmatrix} I & 0 \\ A_{21}A_{11}^{-1} & I \end{pmatrix}
\begin{pmatrix} A_{11} & A_{12} \\ 0 & S \end{pmatrix}
\]
where $S = A_{22} - A_{21}A_{11}^{-1}A_{12}$ is the **Schur complement**.
